abstract.p:
A handpiece for dental or surgical applications, comprising a

- a chuck (2) for rotatably clamping a tool such as a bur, the chuck (2) being drivingly connectable to a drive mechanism such as to rotate said tool about a rotation axis (R) thereof;

- a push button (5) operatively connected to said chuck (2), configured to release said tool from the chuck (2) upon depressing the push button (5);

- a spherical element, preferably a ball (7), is fitted within or mounted at the push button (5), arranged and configured such that - when the push button (5) is depressed - the spherical element (7) enters into contact with the chuck (2), said spherical element comprising a material with a high hardness on the Vickers scale of > 2'000..

A handpiece for dental or surgical applications, comprising a 
- a chuck (2) for rotatably clamping a tool such as a bur, the chuck (2) being drivingly connectable to a drive mechanism such as to rotate said tool about a rotation axis (R) thereof; 
- a push button (5) operatively connected to said chuck (2), configured to release said tool from the chuck (2) upon depressing the push button (5); 
- a spherical element, preferably a ball (7), is fitted within or mounted at the push button (5), arranged and configured such that - when the push button (5) is depressed - the spherical element (7) enters into contact with the chuck (2), said spherical element comprising a material with a high hardness on the Vickers scale of > 2'000..

description.p:
Several alternative approaches have been developed to overcome the problem such as:
integrating a ball bearing in the Push-Button and using the inner and outer ring of the ball bearing to insulate the push-button from heat-transmission. However, in addition to being an expensive solution, the ball bearing is used in a way that leads to fast wear-out of the ball bearing;
Providing the chuck mechanism with a rounded end in hard metal. However, due to the large geometry, the heat protection of this design is very limited.

claim.claim-text:
A handpiece (10) for dental or surgical applications, comprising a
- a chuck (2) for rotatably clamping a tool (100) such as a bur, the chuck (2) being drivingly connectable to a drive mechanism such as to rotate said tool (100) about a rotation axis (R) thereof;
- a push button (5) operatively connected to said chuck (2), configured to release said tool (100) from the chuck (2) upon depressing the push button (5);
characterized in that:
- a spherical element, preferably a ball (7), is fitted within or mounted at the push button (5), arranged and configured such that - when the push button (5) is depressed - the spherical element (7) enters into contact with the chuck (2),
- said spherical element comprising a material with a high hardness on the Vickers scale of > 2'000.
